USER CONSTRAINT (2026-06-02): browser housekeeping must NOT rely on system chrome or a raw OS chrome.exe process query - it must rely on HOW PLAYWRITER does it. The orphan-reap and the spawn-vs-reuse decision must go through playwriter native session lifecycle (runBrowserRunner pw session list/close/new --direct wsEndpoint) and playwriter own chromium (the ms-playwright managed binary via startManagedBrowser/findInstalledChromiumBinary), never Get-CimInstance chrome.exe / pgrep chrome. The reaper I drafted (listChromeProcsByProfileRoot via powershell Get-CimInstance) violates this - it must be redesigned to enumerate+close sessions the playwriter way (by wsEndpoint/profileDir that playwriter owns), or to kill only the pid tree that startManagedBrowser itself recorded, reconciled against playwriter session list.